<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idd10343ef-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e" identifier="/us/usc/t50/s854"><num value="854">§ 854.</num><heading> Rules, regulations, and forms</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Attorney General may at any time, make, prescribe, amend, and rescind such rules, regulations and forms as he deems necessary to carry out the provisions of this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idd10343f0-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e">(<ref href="/us/act/1956-08-01/ch849/s5">Aug. 1, 1956, ch. 849, § 5</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/70/900">70 Stat. 900</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idd10343f1-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idd10343f2-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="idd10343f3-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was not enacted as part of the Internal Security Act of 1950 which comprises subchapters I to III of this chapter.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
